The Ministry of Foreign Affairs and the Ministry of Education and Culture do not celebrate Christmas at all, have communicated to [origo] the respective press services.
The press service of the Ministry of the Environment did not know the price of the official Christmas party.
However, more than 400 people were invited to the festival at the Museum of Decorative Art.
The forces of the mega strike gather
On Friday, the unions of the League and the National Association of Workers' Councils will set up their strike commission, which will be responsible for coordinating the indefinite strike of Monday.
On Saturday, a general assembly of protest will be held and on Monday, the day of the final vote on the law on health funds, the strike will begin.
This action will certainly cause major traffic bottlenecks because rail traffic will be stopped almost completely and BKV employees (public transport company) will also strike until 1 p.m.
On Friday afternoon, the league unions will make known the details of their Monday strike, organised with the National Association of Workers' Councils.
The strike commission of LIGA - MOSZ will also be formed, it will serve as coordinator of the actions of Monday.
On Saturday, a general protest assembly will be held and, starting on Monday, the organisations joining the strike will stop work for an indefinite period if they fail to reach an agreement with the government.
This means that the date of the end of the strike, from the day of the vote in parliament on the law on health funds, is not defined.
If the National Assembly does not adopt the law on health funds, the unions will immediately withdraw the call for a strike.
On the other hand, if the law is passed, the strike commissions will meet and decide what action to take.
According to Monday's agenda of the National Assembly, it is likely that the vote on the Health Fund Act will take place only late in the evening or even at night.
As a result of the strike scheduled for Monday, major traffic stops are planned: the railways will stop work for an indefinite period and during the morning part of the public transport in Budapest and more than half of the companies Volán are at risk of being stopped.
At the same time, at different points in the country, half of the road will also be blocked.
Many trade unions and civil organizations have joined the call for strikes, the list of them is constantly updated on the website of the League.
Some organizations report an indefinite strike, while others report a temporary stoppage of work.
Until Thursday afternoon the MÁV (Hungarian Railways) and the Free Trade Union of Railway Workers (VDSZSZ) failed to reach an agreement on the minimum services, but as Christmas holidays approached, more and more people are taking the train.
According to current communications, public transport in Budapest will strike from the start of service until 1 p.m., Budapest airport between 7 a.m. and 9 a.m., the Industrial Unions of Electricity and Thermal Energy of the League will strike for four hours, the Union of Teachers and the Democratic Union of Teachers have called to strike for two hours and from 2 a.m. to 8 a.m. respectively.
The National Association of Physicians will strike across the country alternately, the Union of Health and Social Workers (EDDSZ) attached to the SZEF will make a warning strike of two hours.
The most important of the four demands made by the League requires the Government to withdraw its proposal on health reform and to submit a new vision to social debate.
The second claim requires that the new method of calculating retirement to be introduced from next year be introduced in several stages.
The third claim is for a guarantee of retirement before the legal age, which would allow the system to pass on the functions that deserve it before 2010.
The fourth reason for the action is the rejection by the Free Trade Union of Railway Workers (VDSZSZ), attached to the Syndicates of the League, of the proposal of the Ministry of Economy and Transport concerning secondary railway lines and the expectation of another proposal.
Political Capital: Hungarian Guard increased country risk
According to the Risk Analysis Division of Political Capital, the activity of the Hungarian Guard, established last August, with the support of Jobbik Magyarországert Mozgalom (Movement for a better Hungary), is increasing, in several ways, the political risk of Hungary and the region.
In its "risk warning", society points out that, in relation to the activity of the Hungarian Guard, the greatest political risk is already that "in the short term aggressive ethnic confrontations can occur as a result of the worsening ethnic tension already existing between the Gypsy and non-gypsy population of Hungary".
The research institute added that the Hungarian Guard's political strategy to provoke this situation is probably the main reason.
As they say, this is due to one of the main shortcomings of Hungarian political actors: "public actors have passed the public debate on the Roma case to representatives of radical and extreme political groupings which have based a political strategy on the dispute between Gypsies and Hungarians".
The problem is compounded, normal dialogue becomes impossible, extremists are reinforced and the advent of aggressive conflicts is more likely, they say.
However, according to the research institute, the Hungarian Guard's activity "has significantly deteriorated Hungary's image abroad, in particular with regard to confidence in the country's stability and democratic maturity, as a result of the increased attention of the Hungarian and international media."
They recall that, following greater publicity given to the reorganization of the radical and extreme right Hungarian groups since autumn 2006, many associations have been formed in Hungary since the summer of 2007 calling themselves a "national self-defence association".
"The common feature of these rallies is that they define themselves as a civil organization when they publicly declare the preparation of their members for defence missions (catastrophes, national defence, defence of order), armed if it is necessary, moreover, by referring to the incapacity of the police, of the army, in other words of the state," they added.
They pointed out that everything was going according to the method which, based on the resentment of the political society and the parties, sought to disguise different political ambitions in a civilian way.
