The British teacher tried in Sudan for insulting Islam was sentenced Thursday night by a court in Khartoum to 15 days in prison and deportation, said her lawyer.
The British were accused of letting students between the ages of 6 and 7 give Mohammed's name to a teddy bear while any representation of the prophet of Islam is illegal.
