What assurance does it suit me?
Car insurance, which covers the driver in the face of possible claims, involves a significant expenditure which will depend on various factors, such as age, sex, seniority of the driver's licence, marital status, type of vehicle to be carried out or the use made of it, among others.
Having a car is the main thing.
Y es que, escoger el seguro de automóvil adecuado es includedo más difícil que elegir el modelo de vehículo.
And it's that, choosing the right car insurance, is even more difficult than choosing the model of the vehicle.
Car insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and the insurer.
This compromise is embodied in an insurance contract, which establishes that the company receives the value of the premium awarded and in return becomes responsible for the obligation to pay compensation in the event of a loss.
The premium is the price of insurance, which takes into account various factors, such as age, sex, seniority of the driver's licence, marital status, type of vehicle to be used or the use made of it, among others.
Insurance companies set their prices on the basis of statistics, so that the higher the probability of an accident, the higher the rating.
This is why people over the age of 25 and women have to pay lower premiums, since statistics show that these people have a lower rate of claims due to their prudence.
Similarly, by using censuses, the companies concluded that married people tend to have fewer accidents than single drivers.
The use of the vehicle will affect the frequency, and therefore the likelihood of an accident.
By increasing the frequency the probabilities increase.
There are many of the variables that insurers take into account when setting the premium price.
For this reason, the driver must study the situation well in order to choose the car insurance that best fits his profile.
We will present here the most significant variables when choosing one or the other type of insurance, so that it, in addition to adapting to the characteristics of the insurer, offers it a reasonable price.
Young people under the age of 25 face various disadvantages when entering into a contract with insurance at an affordable price, as may be the low experience in driving and seniority of a driver's licence.
Although the ideal to be well insured is insurance at any risk, other more cost-effective options exist.
The most prudent drivers can opt for any-risk insurance with a franchise, so that they get coverage for any-risk insurance at a more accessible price.
This form of agreement implies that the customer pays part of the amount of the claim.
"The part of the amount of the claim paid by the customer will be based on the value of the premium, which will be higher and the amount will be lower," says Luis Noguera, the Spanish manager of First Europa, an online insurance mediator.
Another option is extended third-party insurance, so that the customer provides protection to deal with damage caused to third parties, but by those caused on his own car.
In addition, it would be covered against theft, fire and loss of the vehicle.
A piece of advice.
If you are under 25 years of age try to be careful and avoid claims as far as possible, since this will affect the bonus, which can reduce the insurance price in the future.
A bonus is a reduction in the company's basic rate.
On the contrary, a penalty is an increase in the basic tariff.
"Enhancements and sanctions will depend on the company and its profit.
If the company had a good year it will be able to afford to increase the bonuses ", enlightens Noguera.
After 25 years, it becomes easier for drivers to make a contract with insurance, since the rate of claims is reduced thanks to the accumulated experience.
It is for this reason that it is preferable to choose any risk insurance with franchise.
"Normally young people cannot take advantage of the previous experience gained after an accident", says the director of the European company in Spain and adds that the majority of accidents occur during the second year of driving, once the 'fear of the novice' has passed.
However, if the client is married but does not yet have children, it is preferable to negotiate insurance at any risk, as long as his or her economic situation permits.
Marriages with children are considered by insurers to be those with the lowest rate of claims, because the increases will be lower.
In this case the best insurance would be any risk insurance with deductible (may be 300 euros), or a third-party insurance extended from the third year of life of the vehicle when the insured has a high level of bonus.
"They have a more relaxed drive and they have greater purchasing power to afford the luxury to assume a larger amount of franchises," says Luis Noguera.
For retirees, insurance at any risk with a deductible is preferable (by being 150 euros), or extended third-party insurance when the insurer has a high level of bonus.
It must be said that motor insurance is something important, not only because it covers the driver in the face of possible losses, but also because it represents a major expense, which is why it is essential to study properly the insurance that suits us most according to our personal situation.
